  "texts": [
    "However, it remains largely unclear which factors and variables drive the level of (in)efficiency in this young market.",
    "This study examines the time-varying adjusted magnitude market inefficiency (AMIM) measure, recently introduced by Le Tran and Leirvik (2019), to study the two largest CCs, Bitcoin and Ethereum.",
    "Second, we apply the quantile regression (QR) model to understand the drivers of AMIMs, using a large set of explanatory variables reflecting the internal and external characteristics of the CC markets.",
    "We use the QR model to account for the evolution of AMIM measures and their recurrent shifts from a situation in which the markets studied are efficient to one in which these markets are inefficient.",
    "The results suggest that the two CC markets exhibit a time-varying efficiency pattern, as indicated by an alternation between periods of efficiency and inefficiency."
  ],
